  "title": "Least Upper Bound Property",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(S,\\le)$ be an ordered set. The set $S$ has the \\emph{Least Upper Bound Property} if and only if every nonempty subset of $S$ that is bounded above in $S$ has a supremum in $S$.",
